'''''Navio da República Portuguesa''''' ([[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] for "Ship of the Portuguese Republic"), abbreviated as '''N.R.P.''' or '''NRP''', is a [[ship prefix]] used to identify a [[ship commissioning|commissioned]] ship of the [[Portuguese Navy]].

During the [[Kingdom of Portugal|Portuguese Monarchy era]], there was not a standard method of referring to the Royal Portuguese Navy's ships. After the [[5 October 1910 revolution|establishment of the Portuguese Republic on 5 October 1910]], all the Portuguese Navy's naval ships started to be officially referred by her name preceded by ''Navio da República Portuguesa'' or its abbreviation.

After July 1981, the Portuguese Navy's vessels not considered as naval ships came to be officially referred to by the prefix ''Unidade Auxiliar da Marinha'' (Navy's Auxiliary Unit), abbreviated as U.A.M. or UAM.

Sometimes, some of Navy Portuguese vessels are referred by alternative prefixes that indicate their function or type, as N.E. for ''Navio-Escola'' ([[training ship|school ship]]) or N.H. for ''Navio Hidrográfico'' ([[Research vessel#Hydrographic survey|hydrographic ship]]). For example, although the official name of the school ship ''[[NRP Sagres III|Sagres]]'' be N.R.P. ''Sagres'', is occasionally referred to as N.E. ''Sagres''.

