The '''''Pergamon World Atlas''''' (in English, 1968) was originally prepared by the [[Polish Army]] Topographical Service.<ref>{{cite book|author=American Association for the Advancement of Science|title=Science books: a quarterly review|volume=4|year=1968|publisher=American Association for the Advancement of Science.|page=319}}</ref> It was published as the '''''Atlas Świata''''' (World Atlas) in 1962.

The [[atlas (cartography)|atlas]] contains 380 pages of maps, figures and tables along with an index of 150,000 entries. Each geographic map is accompanied by a selection of [[thematic map]]s and [[city map]]s. The ''Pergamon'' added extra maps of the United Kingdom and Canada.

